author: Special to the Courier
title: Osen, Hulse lead Viking harriers
text: Osen, Hulse lead Viking harriers Special to the Courier winfieldcourier.com | 0 comments The Winfield High School cross country teams traveled to El Dorado Lake Saturday for the El Dorado Invitational. Twenty schools competed in the meet, with the majority of the teams being class 5A-6A. Wichita East won the varsity boys division while Bishop Carroll won the girls division. The Viking girls placed 10th out of the twenty schools. The boys did not field a varsity team. Senior standout Riley Osen won the varsity boys race by twenty seconds over second place Marcus Tula of Garden City. Osen’s time of 15:39 was just off his course and meet record he set last year. Osen surged just past the mile mark and increased his lead through the next two miles for a comfortable win. Bri Hulse led the girls team with a school-record effort of 20:59 for the 5,000 meter course. Hulse and Sierra Salsman were co-owners of the school record this year at 21:53, as the 5K race is new for high school girls competition. Hulse’s efforts placed her in the top 25 as she medaled in the meet to place 21st overall among the 118 runners. Five of the seven Viking girls had personal best efforts for the day. Kallie McNutt shattered her personal best by one and a half minutes, running number two for the Vikings and placing 47th with 21:56. Sierra Salsman was next as she placed 54th at 22:02. Emma Smith turned in a personal best of 22:32 for 69th. Brianna Dutton ran number five for Winfield, taking 78th with a 22:55 for the 5K course.
